str] | None = None):\n    self.args = self.parser.parse_args(args)\n    return self.args\n```\n\n- Accepts optional `args` parameter for testing\n- Allows passing test arguments without relying on sys.argv\n\n### Test Results\n```\n\u2705 test_full_flow - PASSED\n\u2705 test_parse_docs - PASSED  \n\u2705 test_type_to_argparse - PASSED\n\u2705 test_is_optional - PASSED\n\u2705 test_lists - PASSED\n\u2705 test_paths - PASSED\n\n6 passed in 0.02s\n```\n\nAll tests pass with no regressions. The implementation correctly handles:\n- List-of-numbers parameters as `list[int]`\n- Optional list-of-paths parameters as `list[Path]` or `None`\n- Function invocation and result return\n- Both synchronous and asynchronous functions",
